{"cursor":"8503","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"'Fancy pigeons' are domesticated varieties of the Rock Pigeon. They are bred by\npigeon fanciers for various traits relating to size, shape, color, and\nbehavior, who often exhibit their birds at pigeon shows,\nfairs and other livestock exhibits.\n\nThere are about 800 pigeon breeds; considering all regional varieties all over\nthe world there may be 1100 breeds. The European list of fancy\npigeons alone names about 500 breeds. No other domestic animal has\nbranched out into such a variety of forms and colours.\n\nCharles Darwin is known to have crossbred fancy pigeons, particularly the Ice\nPigeon, to study variation within species, this work coming three\nyears before his groundbreaking publication, [[On the Origin of Species]].\n","linknr":-1,"url":"fancy_pigeon","recorded":1376428051,"links":[],"instances":["pigeon","pigeon","pigeon","pigeon","food","pigeon","pigeon","pigeon","pigeon","pigeon","pigeon","pigeon","pigeon"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Aviculture","Columba (genus)","Domesticated animals","Domestic pigeons"],"headings":["Pigeon showing","Major breed families of fancy pigeon","See also","References","External links"],"image":[],"tags":[["fantail","pigeon"],["jacobin","pigeon"],["lahore","pigeon"],["trumpeter","pigeon"],["archangel","pigeon"],["starling","pigeon"],["dragoon","pigeon"],["helmet","pigeon"],["nun","pigeon"],["roller","pigeon"],["squab","food"],["king","pigeon"],["strasser","pigeon"]],"members":["lahore","fantail","helmet","dragoon","squab","nun","archangel","roller","strasser","king","trumpeter","jacobin","starling"],"related":["Domestication","Rock_Dove","Pigeon_keeping","Livestock_show","Charles_Darwin","Ice_Pigeon","Blackpool","Royal_Pigeon_Racing_Association","Nuremberg","Louisville,_Kentucky","Asia","Fantail_(pigeon)","Frillback","Jacobin_(pigeon)","Lahore_(pigeon)","Trumpeter_(pigeon)","Archangel_(pigeon)","Danish_Suabian","Saxon_Field_Pigeon","Starling_(pigeon)","Saxon